scopecontent.p:
This portion of the collection contains material documenting the professional and personal life of the D'Aulaires. The acquisition largely includes material surrounding the D'Aulaires' publications -- such as correspondence and reviews -- rather than extensive materials from the production of their books. There are some documents, such as drafts and proofs, relating to unpublished works and works published in German and in English. Material relating to the D'Aulaire's artwork can be found in sketches, drawings, and various objects relating to the artistic process, such as painter's palettes and other art supplies. Other Papers also includes correspondence and photographs relating to the D'Aulaires' personal life and Objects includes personal effects (such as eyeglasses). Audiovisual Material, largely home movies and a documentary film about the D'Aulaires (
                     Children of the Northlights
                  ), similarly provides insight into the D'Aulaires' lives and careers.
